PROJECT 1: ReimbursementSystem

Used Dependencies:
    Libraries:
        *ojdbc8-12.2.0.1.jar
        *postgresql-42.2.1.jre7.jar
        javax.servlet-api-4.0.0.jar
        jsoup-1.11.2.jar
        commons-io-2.6.jar
        commons-fileupload-1.3.3.jar
    Servers:
        Apache Tomcat v9.0 Server
        PostgreSQL v10.1
    Browsers Tested On:
        Opera
    
    * These jars are expected to be placed in <tomcat>/lib/ folder.
    
Start page: <host>:<port>/reimbursement/
        or  <host>:<port>/reimbursement/login
        
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Database-related files:
    database.properties 
        - located in src/main/resources
        - If not connecting to the database using SSL, comment out the SSL-related lines.
    rds-combined-ca-bundle.pem (for connecting to the database using SSL)
        - located in src/main/resources
    Scripts:
        - located in ./scripts/
        - [aws-pgsql]
            - script for logging into AWS PostgreSQL database in command line (using psql)
        - [local-pgsql]
            - script for logging into localhost PostgreSQL database in command line (using psql)
        - [dbcreate]
            - installs extensions, tables, fixed table entries, and functions/procedures
        - [dbclean]
            - drops all tables and functions created by [dbcreate]
        - [dispall]
            - displays info about all the records in the tables
        - [dispusr]
            - displays the user table
        - [dispr]
            - displays reimbursement table info
            - info is modified slightly to show more useful info about the receipt data
        
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
[psql] command line options notes:
    - [-h host]: database server host, default is localhost
    - [-p port]: database port, default is 5432
    - [-U username]: database username
    - [-d sid/database name]: name of the database (SID)
    
[psql] some useful commands:
    - \i <script file>
        - runs the given SQL script
    - \connect <database name>
        - connects to the specified database
    - \? 
        - lists commands & info about them
    - \d[+] [name]
        - lists all databases, provides more info if [+] is specified
        - if [name] is specified, shows info about the specified database
    - \df [pattern]
        - lists functions in database
        - the list is filtered by the given [pattern] if provided; accepts wildcards
    - \dn [pattern]
        - list schemas
    - \dp [pattern]
        - list table/view/sequence access privileges
    - \dy [pattern]
        - list event triggers
    - \l
        - list databases
    - \! [command]
        - execute shell command
    - \q
        - Exits psql
        
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
To view PostgreSQL databases in Oracle SQL Developer...
    1) Tools > Preferences > Database > Third Party JDBC Drivers
        > Add Entry... > [path to postgresql-42.2.1.jre7.jar]
    2) Create New Database Connection
        - Connection Name: ...
        - Username: [database username]
        - Password: [database password]
        - Select PostgreSQL
            - Hostname: [url]/[Database Name/SID]?
            - Port: [port, default is 5432]
        

